value.0: The basilisk is a reptilian monster that is justly feared for its ability to petrify living creatures with a mere glance.  Basilisks are omnivorous and able to consume their petrified victims.  A basilisk usually has a dull brown body with a yellowish underbelly.  A single row of bony spines lines its back, and some specimens sport a short, curved horn atop the nose.  The creature's most distinctive feature is its eyes, which glow with an eerie, pale green incandescence.
